     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="7"/>
   <head>A <hi>Valeto</hi> to the Praeparatiue.</head>
   <l>God guide thee well my Praepratiue,</l>
   <l>to peace and <hi>Contentation:</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Thus now at length, as needfull is,</l>
   <l>compos'd in contemplation:</l>
   <l>The Turke and Pope will freat and threat,</l>
   <l>the glorious Pharisee:</l>
   <l>The Sectaries, and Scismatikes</l>
   <l>will burne and banish thee.</l>
   <l>The Epicures Cyclopicall</l>
   <l>will grunt at thee lyke Hogges:</l>
   <l>And all the godlesse Atheists will</l>
   <l>against thee barke as Dogges:</l>
   <l>But feare them not, whiles truth and fayth</l>
   <l>and reason can thee stay:</l>
   <l>And for thy good successe, to God</l>
   <l>the Christians true shall pray.</l>
   <l>Adieu therefore, prepare the mindes</l>
   <l>of men, to <hi>Contentation:</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Especially my Countrey-men,</l>
   <l>I meane, the English Nation.</l>
   <trailer>Vale.</trailer>
</div>
